          "body": "Verse 28 is the chapter's doctrinal apex. Three theological loads sit on a single line. (1) **Pastoral office is divinely instituted** — the Holy Spirit, not the apostle, has *made* (*etheto*) these men overseers. Apostolic appointment ratified, did not create, what the Spirit had done. (2) **One office, three terms** — these *presbuteroi* (v.17) are *episkopoi* (v.28) commanded to *poimaino* (v.28). Elder, overseer, and pastor are one role under three vocabularies, decisive against any tiered hierarchy. (3) **The church belongs to God, purchased with His own blood** — possibly the strongest atonement statement in Acts. The textual issue ('church of God' / 'church of the Lord') and the syntax of *dia tou haimatos tou idiou* ('through the blood of His Own') open onto the deity of Christ: the blood of God's Own Son is, in the deepest sense, God's own blood (cf. 1 Corinthians 2:8)."
